# 1. Overview

This document defines the core business entities of the MVP.

Each entity represents a business concept that will later become database models, backend entities, and API resources.

---

# 2. Core Entities

## User

### Purpose

Represents a registered platform account.

### Owns

- Profile
- Goals
- Measurements
- Progress
- Subscription

### Relationships

User
- has one Profile
- has many Goals
- has many Measurements
- has many Progress Records
- has one Subscription
- belongs to zero or more Programs

---

## Profile

### Purpose

Stores personal information required for personalization.

### Examples

- Age
- Height
- Weight
- Gender
- Fitness Level

---

## Program

### Purpose

Represents a structured journey toward a health objective.

### Types

- Workout Program
- Nutrition Program

---

## Program Item

### Purpose

Represents a single activity inside a Program.

Examples

- Workout
- Lesson
- Daily Task

---

## Content

### Purpose

Educational resources used inside Programs.

### Types

- Video
- Course
- Collection

---

## Progress

### Purpose

Stores user progress across Programs and Content.

### Relationships

Progress belongs to:

- User
- Program
- Content
---

## Measurement

### Purpose

Stores user body measurements over time.

---

## Goal

### Purpose

Represents a measurable objective defined by the user.

Examples

- Lose Weight
- Gain Muscle
- Improve Endurance

---

## Professional

### Purpose

Represents a Trainer or Nutritionist assigned to users.

---

## Subscription

### Purpose

Defines user access level.

### Types

- Free
- Premium

